toon.library/ToonEncode                             toon.library/ToonEncode

   NAME
        ToonEncode -- convert a JSON string to TOON format

   SYNOPSIS
        toon = ToonEncode(json, indent, delimiter)
        D0                A0    D0      D1

        char *ToonEncode(const char *, int, int);

   FUNCTION
        Parses a JSON string and encodes it as TOON (Token-Oriented Object
        Notation) text. The input must be valid JSON.

   INPUTS
        json - a NUL-terminated JSON string to convert
        indent - number of spaces per indentation level (0 = use default 2)
        delimiter - array delimiter style:
                    TOON_DELIM_COMMA (0) - comma-separated (default)
                    TOON_DELIM_TAB   (1) - tab-separated
                    TOON_DELIM_PIPE  (2) - pipe-separated

   RESULT
        toon - a NUL-terminated string containing the TOON representation,
               or NULL if the JSON input could not be parsed.
               The caller must free this string with ToonFreeString().

   SEE ALSO
        ToonDecode(), ToonEncodeValue(), ToonFreeString()


toon.library/ToonDecode                             toon.library/ToonDecode

   NAME
        ToonDecode -- convert a TOON string to JSON format

   SYNOPSIS
        json = ToonDecode(toon, indent, strict)
        D0                A0    D0      D1

        char *ToonDecode(const char *, int, int);

   FUNCTION
        Parses a TOON string and emits the equivalent JSON text.

   INPUTS
        toon - a NUL-terminated TOON string to convert
        indent - expected indentation width (0 = use default 2)
        strict - if non-zero, reject non-conforming input

   RESULT
        json - a NUL-terminated JSON string, or NULL on parse error.
               The caller must free this string with ToonFreeString().

   SEE ALSO
        ToonEncode(), ToonDecodeValue(), ToonFreeString()


toon.library/ToonDecodeValue                   toon.library/ToonDecodeValue

   NAME
        ToonDecodeValue -- decode TOON text to a JsonValue tree

   SYNOPSIS
        val = ToonDecodeValue(toon, indent, strict, err)
        D0                    A0    D0      D1      A1

        JsonValue ToonDecodeValue(const char *, int, int, const char **);

   FUNCTION
        Parses TOON text and returns a JsonValue tree that can be
        inspected and manipulated with the ToonGetType, ToonArrayItem,
        ToonObjectSet family of functions.

   INPUTS
        toon - a NUL-terminated TOON string
        indent - expected indentation width (0 = use default 2)
        strict - if non-zero, reject non-conforming input
        err - pointer to a const char* that will receive an error message
              on failure, or NULL if no error reporting is needed

   RESULT
        val - a JsonValue handle, or NULL on parse error.
              The caller must free this value with ToonFreeValue().

   SEE ALSO
        ToonEncodeValue(), ToonFreeValue(), ToonGetType()


toon.library/ToonEncodeValue                   toon.library/ToonEncodeValue

   NAME
        ToonEncodeValue -- encode a JsonValue tree as TOON text

   SYNOPSIS
        toon = ToonEncodeValue(val, indent, delimiter)
        D0                     A0   D0      D1

        char *ToonEncodeValue(JsonValue, int, int);

   FUNCTION
        Takes a JsonValue tree (constructed via ToonNewObject, ToonNewArray,
        etc. or obtained from ToonDecodeValue/ToonParseJSON) and produces
        the TOON text representation.

   INPUTS
        val - a JsonValue handle to encode
        indent - number of spaces per indentation level (0 = use default 2)
        delimiter - array delimiter style (TOON_DELIM_COMMA, etc.)

   RESULT
        toon - a NUL-terminated TOON string, or NULL on error.
               The caller must free this string with ToonFreeString().

   SEE ALSO
        ToonDecodeValue(), ToonEncode(), ToonFreeString()


toon.library/ToonGet                                   toon.library/ToonGet

   NAME
        ToonGet -- query a value from a TOON document by path

   SYNOPSIS
        result = ToonGet(toon, path, format)
        D0                A0    A1    D0

        char *ToonGet(const char *, const char *, int);

   FUNCTION
        Decodes a TOON document and extracts the value at the given
        dotted path. For primitive values (null, bool, number, string),
        returns the bare text representation. For complex values (arrays,
        objects), the output format depends on the format argument.

        The path uses dotted notation: "server.host" walks into nested
        objects. Array indices use dotted numbers: "users.0.name".
        A path of "." returns the root value.

   INPUTS
        toon - a NUL-terminated TOON string
        path - a NUL-terminated dotted path string, or "." for root
        format - output format for complex values:
                 TOON_FMT_AUTO (0) - primitives bare, complex as TOON
                 TOON_FMT_JSON (1) - always JSON
                 TOON_FMT_TOON (2) - always TOON

   RESULT
        result - a NUL-terminated string containing the value, or NULL
                 if the path was not found or the document could not be
                 parsed. The caller must free this string with
                 ToonFreeString().

   EXAMPLE
        /* Read a nested value */
        result = ToonGet(toon_text, "server.host", TOON_FMT_AUTO);
        if (result) {
            Printf("Host: %s\n", result);
            ToonFreeString(result);
        }

   SEE ALSO
        ToonSet(), ToonDel(), ToonFreeString()


toon.library/ToonSet                                   toon.library/ToonSet

   NAME
        ToonSet -- set a value in a TOON document by path

   SYNOPSIS
        result = ToonSet(toon, path, value)
        D0                A0    A1    A2

        char *ToonSet(const char *, const char *, const char *);

   FUNCTION
        Decodes a TOON document, sets the value at the given dotted path,
        and re-encodes the result as TOON text.

        The value string is auto-detected: "true"/"false" become booleans,
        "null" becomes null, strings starting with { [ or " are parsed as
        JSON, numeric strings become numbers, and everything else becomes
        a string. Missing intermediate objects are created automatically.

        A path of "." replaces the entire root value.

   INPUTS
        toon - a NUL-terminated TOON string
        path - a NUL-terminated dotted path string
        value - a NUL-terminated string representation of the new value

   RESULT
        result - a NUL-terminated TOON string containing the updated
                 document, or NULL on error. The caller must free this
                 string with ToonFreeString().

   SEE ALSO
        ToonGet(), ToonDel(), ToonFreeString()


toon.library/ToonDel                                   toon.library/ToonDel

   NAME
        ToonDel -- delete a value from a TOON document by path

   SYNOPSIS
        result = ToonDel(toon, path)
        D0                A0    A1

        char *ToonDel(const char *, const char *);

   FUNCTION
        Decodes a TOON document, removes the value at the given dotted
        path, and re-encodes the result as TOON text. For arrays,
        deleting an element shifts subsequent elements down.

   INPUTS
        toon - a NUL-terminated TOON string
        path - a NUL-terminated dotted path to the value to remove

   RESULT
        result - a NUL-terminated TOON string containing the updated
                 document, or NULL if the path was not found or the
                 document could not be parsed. The caller must free
                 this string with ToonFreeString().

   SEE ALSO
        ToonGet(), ToonSet(), ToonFreeString()


toon.library/ToonNewNull                           toon.library/ToonNewNull

   NAME
        ToonNewNull -- create a new JSON null value

   SYNOPSIS
        val = ToonNewNull()
        D0

        JsonValue ToonNewNull(void);

   FUNCTION
        Allocates and returns a new JsonValue representing JSON null.

   INPUTS
        None.

   RESULT
        val - a JsonValue handle, or NULL if memory allocation failed.
              The caller must free this value with ToonFreeValue().

   SEE ALSO
        ToonNewBool(), ToonNewNumber(), ToonNewString(), ToonFreeValue()


toon.library/ToonNewBool                           toon.library/ToonNewBool

   NAME
        ToonNewBool -- create a new JSON boolean value

   SYNOPSIS
        val = ToonNewBool(bval)
        D0                D0

        JsonValue ToonNewBool(int);

   FUNCTION
        Allocates and returns a new JsonValue representing a JSON boolean.

   INPUTS
        bval - boolean value: 0 for false, non-zero for true

   RESULT
        val - a JsonValue handle, or NULL if memory allocation failed.
              The caller must free this value with ToonFreeValue().

   SEE ALSO
        ToonGetBool(), ToonNewNull(), ToonFreeValue()


toon.library/ToonNewNumber                       toon.library/ToonNewNumber

   NAME
        ToonNewNumber -- create a new JSON number value

   SYNOPSIS
        val = ToonNewNumber(valptr)
        D0                  A0

        JsonValue ToonNewNumber(double *);

   FUNCTION
        Allocates and returns a new JsonValue representing a JSON number.
        The number is passed as a pointer to a double because 68K register
        calling conventions cannot pass doubles in address or data
        registers.

   INPUTS
        valptr - pointer to a double containing the numeric value

   RESULT
        val - a JsonValue handle, or NULL if memory allocation failed.
              The caller must free this value with ToonFreeValue().

   NOTES
        Numbers are stored as IEEE 754 double-precision floats (64-bit).
        Integer values up to 2^53 are represented exactly.

   SEE ALSO
        ToonGetNumber(), ToonNewNull(), ToonFreeValue()


toon.library/ToonNewString                       toon.library/ToonNewString

   NAME
        ToonNewString -- create a new JSON string value

   SYNOPSIS
        val = ToonNewString(s)
        D0                  A0

        JsonValue ToonNewString(const char *);

   FUNCTION
        Allocates and returns a new JsonValue representing a JSON string.
        The input string is copied; the caller retains ownership of the
        original.

   INPUTS
        s - a NUL-terminated string to use as the value

   RESULT
        val - a JsonValue handle, or NULL if memory allocation failed.
              The caller must free this value with ToonFreeValue().

   SEE ALSO
        ToonGetString(), ToonNewNull(), ToonFreeValue()


toon.library/ToonNewArray                         toon.library/ToonNewArray

   NAME
        ToonNewArray -- create a new empty JSON array

   SYNOPSIS
        val = ToonNewArray()
        D0

        JsonValue ToonNewArray(void);

   FUNCTION
        Allocates and returns a new JsonValue representing an empty
        JSON array. Elements can be added with ToonArrayPush().

   INPUTS
        None.

   RESULT
        val - a JsonValue handle, or NULL if memory allocation failed.
              The caller must free this value with ToonFreeValue().

   SEE ALSO
        ToonArrayPush(), ToonArrayCount(), ToonArrayItem(),
        ToonFreeValue()


toon.library/ToonNewObject                       toon.library/ToonNewObject

   NAME
        ToonNewObject -- create a new empty JSON object

   SYNOPSIS
        val = ToonNewObject()
        D0

        JsonValue ToonNewObject(void);

   FUNCTION
        Allocates and returns a new JsonValue representing an empty
        JSON object. Key-value pairs can be added with ToonObjectSet().

   INPUTS
        None.

   RESULT
        val - a JsonValue handle, or NULL if memory allocation failed.
              The caller must free this value with ToonFreeValue().

   SEE ALSO
        ToonObjectSet(), ToonObjectCount(), ToonObjectKey(),
        ToonObjectItem(), ToonFreeValue()


toon.library/ToonArrayPush                       toon.library/ToonArrayPush

   NAME
        ToonArrayPush -- append an element to a JSON array

   SYNOPSIS
        ToonArrayPush(arr, item)
                      A0   A1

        void ToonArrayPush(JsonValue, JsonValue);

   FUNCTION
        Appends the given JsonValue to the end of the array. After this
        call, the array owns the item; do not free it separately.

   INPUTS
        arr - a JsonValue of type TOON_TYPE_ARRAY
        item - a JsonValue to append (ownership transfers to the array)

   RESULT
        None.

   NOTES
        If arr is not an array, this function does nothing.

   SEE ALSO
        ToonNewArray(), ToonArrayCount(), ToonArrayItem()


toon.library/ToonObjectSet                       toon.library/ToonObjectSet

   NAME
        ToonObjectSet -- set a key-value pair in a JSON object

   SYNOPSIS
        ToonObjectSet(obj, key, val)
                      A0   A1   A2

        void ToonObjectSet(JsonValue, const char *, JsonValue);

   FUNCTION
        Sets or replaces the value associated with the given key in the
        object. The key string is copied. The value's ownership transfers
        to the object. If the key already exists, the previous value is
        freed and replaced.

   INPUTS
        obj - a JsonValue of type TOON_TYPE_OBJECT
        key - a NUL-terminated key string (will be copied)
        val - a JsonValue to associate with the key (ownership transfers
              to the object)

   RESULT
        None.

   SEE ALSO
        ToonNewObject(), ToonObjectCount(), ToonObjectKey(),
        ToonObjectItem()


toon.library/ToonFreeValue                       toon.library/ToonFreeValue

   NAME
        ToonFreeValue -- free a JsonValue tree

   SYNOPSIS
        ToonFreeValue(val)
                      A0

        void ToonFreeValue(JsonValue);

   FUNCTION
        Recursively frees a JsonValue and all its children. After this
        call, the handle is invalid and must not be used.

        For arrays, all contained elements are freed. For objects, all
        keys and values are freed.

   INPUTS
        val - a JsonValue handle to free, or NULL (safe to call with NULL)

   RESULT
        None.

   SEE ALSO
        ToonNewNull(), ToonNewArray(), ToonNewObject(), ToonFreeString()


toon.library/ToonGetType                           toon.library/ToonGetType

   NAME
        ToonGetType -- query the type of a JsonValue

   SYNOPSIS
        type = ToonGetType(val)
        D0                 A0

        int ToonGetType(JsonValue);

   FUNCTION
        Returns an integer indicating the JSON type of the given value.

   INPUTS
        val - a JsonValue handle

   RESULT
        type - one of:
               TOON_TYPE_NULL   (0) - JSON null
               TOON_TYPE_BOOL   (1) - JSON boolean
               TOON_TYPE_NUMBER (2) - JSON number
               TOON_TYPE_STRING (3) - JSON string
               TOON_TYPE_ARRAY  (4) - JSON array
               TOON_TYPE_OBJECT (5) - JSON object

               Returns TOON_TYPE_NULL if val is NULL.

   SEE ALSO
        ToonGetString(), ToonGetNumber(), ToonGetBool()


toon.library/ToonGetString                       toon.library/ToonGetString

   NAME
        ToonGetString -- get the string value from a JsonValue

   SYNOPSIS
        s = ToonGetString(val)
        D0                A0

        const char *ToonGetString(JsonValue);

   FUNCTION
        Returns a pointer to the internal string data of a string-type
        JsonValue. The returned pointer is valid for the lifetime of the
        JsonValue. Do not free it; it is freed when ToonFreeValue() is
        called on the owning value.

   INPUTS
        val - a JsonValue of type TOON_TYPE_STRING

   RESULT
        s - a pointer to the NUL-terminated string, or NULL if val is
            not a string type.

   NOTES
        The returned pointer becomes invalid after ToonFreeValue(val).
        Copy the string if you need it to persist.

   SEE ALSO
        ToonNewString(), ToonGetType()


toon.library/ToonGetNumber                       toon.library/ToonGetNumber

   NAME
        ToonGetNumber -- get the numeric value from a JsonValue

   SYNOPSIS
        ok = ToonGetNumber(val, result)
        D0                 A0   A1

        int ToonGetNumber(JsonValue, double *);

   FUNCTION
        Retrieves the numeric value of a number-type JsonValue and stores
        it in the double pointed to by result. Returns a boolean indicating
        success.

   INPUTS
        val - a JsonValue of type TOON_TYPE_NUMBER
        result - pointer to a double to receive the value

   RESULT
        ok - TRUE (non-zero) if val was a number and result was filled,
             FALSE (zero) if val is not a number type.

   SEE ALSO
        ToonNewNumber(), ToonGetType()


toon.library/ToonGetBool                           toon.library/ToonGetBool

   NAME
        ToonGetBool -- get the boolean value from a JsonValue

   SYNOPSIS
        bval = ToonGetBool(val)
        D0                 A0

        int ToonGetBool(JsonValue);

   FUNCTION
        Returns the boolean value of a bool-type JsonValue.

   INPUTS
        val - a JsonValue of type TOON_TYPE_BOOL

   RESULT
        bval - TRUE (non-zero) for JSON true, FALSE (zero) for JSON false.
               Returns FALSE if val is not a boolean type.

   SEE ALSO
        ToonNewBool(), ToonGetType()


toon.library/ToonArrayCount                     toon.library/ToonArrayCount

   NAME
        ToonArrayCount -- get the number of elements in a JSON array

   SYNOPSIS
        count = ToonArrayCount(val)
        D0                     A0

        int ToonArrayCount(JsonValue);

   FUNCTION
        Returns the number of elements in an array-type JsonValue.

   INPUTS
        val - a JsonValue of type TOON_TYPE_ARRAY

   RESULT
        count - the number of elements, or 0 if val is not an array.

   SEE ALSO
        ToonArrayItem(), ToonArrayPush(), ToonNewArray()


toon.library/ToonArrayItem                       toon.library/ToonArrayItem

   NAME
        ToonArrayItem -- get an element from a JSON array by index

   SYNOPSIS
        item = ToonArrayItem(val, index)
        D0                   A0   D0

        JsonValue ToonArrayItem(JsonValue, int);

   FUNCTION
        Returns the JsonValue at the given index in an array. The returned
        value is owned by the array; do not free it directly.

   INPUTS
        val - a JsonValue of type TOON_TYPE_ARRAY
        index - zero-based element index

   RESULT
        item - the JsonValue at that index, or NULL if val is not an
               array or index is out of bounds.

   NOTES
        The returned handle is owned by the parent array. Do not call
        ToonFreeValue() on it. It becomes invalid when the parent is
        freed.

   SEE ALSO
        ToonArrayCount(), ToonArrayPush(), ToonNewArray()


toon.library/ToonObjectCount                   toon.library/ToonObjectCount

   NAME
        ToonObjectCount -- get the number of key-value pairs in a JSON
        object

   SYNOPSIS
        count = ToonObjectCount(val)
        D0                      A0

        int ToonObjectCount(JsonValue);

   FUNCTION
        Returns the number of key-value pairs in an object-type JsonValue.

   INPUTS
        val - a JsonValue of type TOON_TYPE_OBJECT

   RESULT
        count - the number of pairs, or 0 if val is not an object.

   SEE ALSO
        ToonObjectKey(), ToonObjectItem(), ToonObjectSet(), ToonNewObject()


toon.library/ToonObjectKey                       toon.library/ToonObjectKey

   NAME
        ToonObjectKey -- get a key from a JSON object by index

   SYNOPSIS
        key = ToonObjectKey(val, index)
        D0                  A0   D0

        const char *ToonObjectKey(JsonValue, int);

   FUNCTION
        Returns a pointer to the key string at the given index in an
        object. Keys are stored in insertion order.

   INPUTS
        val - a JsonValue of type TOON_TYPE_OBJECT
        index - zero-based pair index

   RESULT
        key - a pointer to the NUL-terminated key string, or NULL if
              val is not an object or index is out of bounds.

   NOTES
        The returned pointer is owned by the object. It becomes invalid
        when the parent is freed or the key is replaced.

   SEE ALSO
        ToonObjectItem(), ToonObjectCount(), ToonObjectSet()


toon.library/ToonObjectItem                     toon.library/ToonObjectItem

   NAME
        ToonObjectItem -- get a value from a JSON object by index

   SYNOPSIS
        item = ToonObjectItem(val, index)
        D0                    A0   D0

        JsonValue ToonObjectItem(JsonValue, int);

   FUNCTION
        Returns the JsonValue associated with the key at the given index
        in an object. Pairs are stored in insertion order.

   INPUTS
        val - a JsonValue of type TOON_TYPE_OBJECT
        index - zero-based pair index

   RESULT
        item - the JsonValue at that index, or NULL if val is not an
               object or index is out of bounds.

   NOTES
        The returned handle is owned by the parent object. Do not call
        ToonFreeValue() on it.

   SEE ALSO
        ToonObjectKey(), ToonObjectCount(), ToonObjectSet()


toon.library/ToonParseJSON                       toon.library/ToonParseJSON

   NAME
        ToonParseJSON -- parse a JSON string into a JsonValue tree

   SYNOPSIS
        val = ToonParseJSON(json, err)
        D0                  A0    A1

        JsonValue ToonParseJSON(const char *, const char **);

   FUNCTION
        Parses a NUL-terminated JSON string and returns a JsonValue tree.
        This is the JSON equivalent of ToonDecodeValue for TOON text.

   INPUTS
        json - a NUL-terminated JSON string
        err - pointer to a const char* that will receive an error message
              on failure, or NULL if no error reporting is needed

   RESULT
        val - a JsonValue handle, or NULL on parse error.
              The caller must free this value with ToonFreeValue().

   SEE ALSO
        ToonEmitJSON(), ToonDecodeValue(), ToonFreeValue()


toon.library/ToonEmitJSON                         toon.library/ToonEmitJSON

   NAME
        ToonEmitJSON -- convert a JsonValue tree to a JSON string

   SYNOPSIS
        json = ToonEmitJSON(val)
        D0                  A0

        char *ToonEmitJSON(JsonValue);

   FUNCTION
        Takes a JsonValue tree and produces a compact JSON string
        representation.

   INPUTS
        val - a JsonValue handle to emit

   RESULT
        json - a NUL-terminated JSON string, or NULL on error.
               The caller must free this string with ToonFreeString().

   SEE ALSO
        ToonParseJSON(), ToonEncodeValue(), ToonFreeString()


toon.library/ToonFreeString                     toon.library/ToonFreeString

   NAME
        ToonFreeString -- free a string returned by the library

   SYNOPSIS
        ToonFreeString(s)
                       A0

        void ToonFreeString(char *);

   FUNCTION
        Frees a NUL-terminated string that was returned by any of the
        library's text-returning functions (ToonEncode, ToonDecode,
        ToonGet, ToonSet, ToonDel, ToonEncodeValue, ToonEmitJSON).

        It is safe to call with NULL.

   INPUTS
        s - a string previously returned by the library, or NULL

   RESULT
        None.

   NOTES
        Do not use C library free() on strings returned by toon.library,
        as the library may use a different memory allocator in future
        versions. Always use ToonFreeString().

   SEE ALSO
        ToonFreeValue(), ToonEncode(), ToonGet()


toon.library/ToonVersion                           toon.library/ToonVersion

   NAME
        ToonVersion -- query the supported TOON specification version

   SYNOPSIS
        version = ToonVersion()
        D0

        int ToonVersion(void);

   FUNCTION
        Returns the TOON specification version that this library
        implements, encoded as major*100 + minor. For example,
        spec version 3.0 returns 300.

   INPUTS
        None.

   RESULT
        version - the spec version as an integer (e.g. 300 for v3.0)

   SEE ALSO
        ToonEncode(), ToonDecode()
